<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>2 SPEED AND DOUBLE REDUCTION SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - ADJUST/INSTALL - INSTALL PINION OIL SEAL AND YOKE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INSTALL PINION OIL SEAL AND YOKE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With pinion bearing preload adjustment complete, install oil seal. Use a press and suitable
                sleeve to prevent distortion or contact with seal lips during installation (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401638">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401638" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401638" filename="../figg14/g1401638.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 38.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure yoke is clean and dry. Install yoke and nut (or nut and washer on some models).
                Tighten nut to correct torque (refer to
                <hotlnk document="s14016_HL1401606.xml" xrefid="hl1401607">Table 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>After tightening nut, recheck pinion bearing torque to rotate, then proceed with pinion
                        installation in carrier.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
